&quot;What changes would YOU like to see to Mod Rods and CoTH to bring the magician class back in line to what we normally do, particularly on raid situations.?&quot;<br>
&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Is both a leading and misleading question, invalidating this as a &quot;survey&quot; - you assume there was some &quot;line&quot; that we have fallen away from, &quot;particularly on raid situations.&quot;<br>
<br>
That's a really dumb question, basically.<br>
<br>
It is wrong.<br>
<br>
Our role in raids hasn't &quot;fallen&quot;, although it has expanded.<br>
<br>
Mala - Damage Shield - Rods - COH on the puller - COH on the raid crew for set up - nukes - Malosi<br>
<br>
Pick a few to do.  They'll keep you busy.  <br>
<br>
Now a new spell or three, that would summon, say five rods at a time, or summon your entire group (this would be of limited effectiveness, though).  Here's a thought - how about a 5000-mana cost Call of the Horde, summon the entire raid party at once?<br>
<br>
That'd sure be curious.<br>
<br>
