<br>
On that note if there was a way we could &quot;sleight of hand&quot; them onto someone's cursor or be given a /drop command that we could simply hot key that would be very helpful.<br>
<br>
I suggest a Staff of Mystical Transvergence<br>
lvl 63<br>
Mana 600<br>
Skill Conjuration<br>
Casting Time 4 seconds<br>
Recast Time 2.25 seconds <br>
The effect of this staff would be a transfer of 400 hitpoints to 350 mana.  The staff should have 7 charges.  At this ratio a fully buffed 60th level magician would be able to convert approximately 90% of thier hit points to about 70% of thier mana.   With the usual exceptions of gear, statistics and Alternative Advancement.  And not a bad option at all when handed to clerics that are likely to have more hitpoints. The staff itself should be LORE and a darn schnazzy 1 handed blunt to boot.<br>
<br>
I suggest this spell because encounters that require modulating rods now are not going to disappear.  An option that would allow more powerful magicians to not have to make as many rods there by allowing them to get back at what they want to do is perfect.  <br>
<br>
I hate mod rods more than anybody.  But I am a team player and if there's a way for me to help my team advance and still enjoy the game I'm playing I'm willing to use it.<br>
<br>
As for Call of the Hero the poor spell has been beaten with the nerf stick enough.  I like the idea of being able to summon an entire group to the magician.  That would be a quite a time and mana saver.<br>
<br>
I would like to see the Anti-Summoning Shield spell that was proposed in beta of Shadows of Luclin then taken out and replaced with the joke of the day Shock of Fiery Blades put back on our spell lists. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufinrazielthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FinrazielTheMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 7:43:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SURVEY III: What changes would YOU like to see to modrod</span><hr size=1> -Call of the Hero is fine as is.<br>
