<br>
Rods could stand some improvements.<br>
<br>
Add a second charge to mod rods to allow them to be used for mana regeneration by younger mages.  Having done the numbers earlier, this is not as gross as it sounds.<br>
<br>
Add the feature that whenever you summon a droppable duplicate lore item, the one you just summoned automatically falls to the ground.<br>
<br>
A /drop command.<br>
<br>
I like the suggestion of targetted summons, and I hate saying that it would be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>too</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> convenient, as if inconvenience was supposed to be a major balancing factor for a spell, but it does seem too good to be true.  Summoning would be as convenient as buffing then.<br>
<br>
I do not think they should be made non-Lore, stackable, or have a higher level multi-charge upgrade, or have a group rod summon.<br>
<br>
Extending the rot timer might be good, but then targetted summons would mostly eliminate the need for that.<br>
<br>
I do think this really belongs in the POLLS section, especially as you have three polls on essentially the same subject, but as it is actively being responded to, I will leave it here for now.<br>
<br>
I expect you to post a clear and concise summary of your results that is of use to someone without slogging through six or more pages of responses.<br>
